// jul19b generate class (5+2 findings across ryouko/katana, all one
// shape: interp quiet at epoch 0, jit fires once). A tail-looped
// callee whose base case bottoms (`1 % 0`) produces a TAINTED
// production at init (in-frame bottoms are tainted; the fd0 filter's
// init-view exemption lets it escape), which poisons the init bind —
// so the fold's INIT arrives tainted rather than absent. FoldQ then
// force-tainted the WHOLE fold, silencing it, where the kernel's
// FoldAcc carries init taint on the acc alone and a callback that
// never consumes the acc recovers (emit_fold_loop's documented rule).
// The depth-0 variant (f(0), no loop) agreed all along — the bottom
// produced None, not a tainted production. Fixed by making FoldQ's
// tainted-init arm a poisoned slot-0 acc delivery (Bind's tainted-arm
// twin); a consuming callback still taints its slot and the
// any-slot-tainted check bottoms the fold.
{
  let rec v1 = |v3: i64| -> i64 select v3 {v4 if v4 <= i64:0 => (i64:1 % v4), v4 => v1(v4 - i64:1)};
  let v5 = v1(i64:1);
  array::fold([i64:1], v5, |v13, v16| v16)
}
